## Conjecture (CPRR)
- Hypothesis 1: the three sage property cages are general patterns
  that apply to any Scheme codebase touching JSON / FFI / filesystem
  boundaries. They should live in hegel-guile as canonical examples
  so other projects can find them and copy the pattern.
- Hypothesis 2: cross-pollination via examples + a pointer doc is
  the lightweight contribution model that makes sense between
  related sibling repos (no shared module deps, just shared test
  patterns and a reference link).
- Hypothesis 3: hegel-guile's hypothesis-backed shrinking is
  particularly valuable for these cages because the failure
  modes (vector-vs-list confusion, inexact-int gotcha,
  filesystem path mangling) are non-obvious counterexamples that
  ad-hoc PRNG harnesses don't minimise. Sage's harness caught the
  bugs but didn't shrink them — the user had to debug from raw
  failures. Hegel would shrink to the smallest counterexample.

